        "title": "How do I download/read html from a website line by line from Android Java App?",
        "body": "<p>I'm currently working on an App that gets a specific text from different sites to process them.\nRight now I'm using:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>URL             textUrl         = new URL(url);\nInputStream     in              = textUrl.openStream();\nBufferedReader  bufferReader    = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(in));\nStringBuilder   stringText      = new StringBuilder();\nString          bufferString;\n\nwhile ((bufferString = bufferReader.readLine()) != null) {\n    if (bufferString.indexOf(\"FIND ME AFTER TEXT\") &gt; -1) {\n        break;\n    }\n    stringText.append(bufferString);\n}\n\nbufferReader.close();\noutput = stringText.toString();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This is, as you might see, downloading the whole html code of the specified page and reads it line by line.<\/p>\n\n<p>But as the specific text that I'm looking for is at the beginning of those pages, my intention is not to only read it line by line, but also download only the line that is currently processed, to save a lot of \"unnecessary\" traffic.<br>\nIs there a way to do this?  If so, how?<\/p>\n\n<p>(Download only specific lines from html pages would be even better, but I guess that IS not possible)<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks in advance.<\/p>\n",
